Home ››Manhattan Active® Omni››Store››Process & Configuration Guides››Point of Sale››POS Classic Guides››POS Metrics and App Reports - Wiretap Strategy ››POS Metrics and Reporting Framework POS Metrics and Reporting Framework Relevant Microservice Components for summary metrics and reporting WiretapCommonUtilReporting FlowData Capture - WiretapData retrieval and Report Generation - CommonUtilEnabling Metrics and Z ReportPOS Dashboard MetricsPOS App Reports Services MAO-POS features a framework for collecting summary metrics on a schedule, and using these for reporting and dashboard-type display within the POS app. Relevant Microservice Components for summary metrics and reporting Wiretap Transactional data capture - The Wiretap component is leveraged to regularly execute SQL queries against customer read replica databases to fetch metric values and populate into Elastic Search. The Wiretap component strategy for Sales Metrics values displayed at POS will be deprecated by first quarter 2025 and replaced with an approach using the Aggregation Framework.  Wiretap will continue to be used for POS App Reporting (Z report). Enable business flag for Z report Use the following API to enable Z report to be triggered by Store Close operation.  This business flag is currently not exposed in any config UI. POST {{url}}/backoffice/api/backoffice/storeReportConfig/save Body { "ReportName": "Z Report", "DependsOnStoreClose": "true", "IsEnabled": true, "ReportLabel": "End Of Day (Z) Report" } 4.  Wiretap Configuration The following two job schedules create the scheduled service to invoke calculation of the metrics and generation of the app reports.   Customize the Cron expression to customize the scheduled runs as desired. In the example below, the ReportMetricsJob is configured to run every 1 minute and collect data retroactively for 2 hour offset. POST : {{url}}/wiretap/api/batch/jobSchedule/save { "JobScheduleId":"wiretapMetricProcessorJob-update_metrics", "JobTypeId":"wiretapMetricProcessorJob", "CronExpression":"0 0 */4 ? * *", "JobParameters":[ { "InputKey":"type", "InputValue":"update_metrics" }, { "InputKey":"duration", "InputValue":"FOUR_HOUR" } ] }, { "JobScheduleId": "ReportMetrics", "JobTypeId": "ReportMetricsJob", "CronExpression": "0 */1 * ? * *", "IsDisabled" : true, "JobParameters": [ { "InputKey": "offsetHoursFromNow", "InputValue": "2" } POS Dashboard Metrics Selected metrics can be exposed on the POS screens for snapshot 'dashboard' display.  See the Metrics sections of POS Selling Process Guide and POS Cart Configuration Guide. User should have appropriate grant. POS App Reports User should have appropriate grants. Currently the only available POS application report is the end of day Z report.  See  the POS Z report guide.
